`test_regex_check.ps1` content:
```powershell
$ScriptName = "coworker.ps1"
$escapedName = [regex]::Escape($ScriptName)
# Regex to match: boundary (start, space, quote, slash, backslash) + name + boundary (end, space, quote)
# Note: dot is NOT a boundary for us (e.g. coworker.ps1.bak should fail)
$pattern = "(?i)(^|[\s""'/\\\\])$escapedName($|[\s""'])"

$inputs = @(
    "D:\path\coworker.ps1",
    ".\coworker.ps1",
    "coworker.ps1",
    "run_coworker_periodically.ps1",
    "my-coworker.ps1",
    "coworker.ps1.bak",
    "coworker.ps11",
    '"D:\path\coworker.ps1"',
    "pwsh -File coworker.ps1"
)

foreach ($i in $inputs) {
    $match = $i -match $pattern
    Write-Host "'$i' -> $match"
}
```

